    "Error Rate",
    "Learning Gain"
  ],
  "GPT51_suggested_pipeline": "- Recruit novice and expert Blender users and randomly assign them to AugGen UI vs default UI conditions.\n- Define a set of 3–5 representative modeling/animation tasks with clearly measurable success criteria.\n- Log interaction data (clicks, commands, navigation events) and record task completion time and errors for each participant.\n- After each task, administer NASA TLX to measure perceived cognitive load.\n- Before and after the session, administer a short concept test on Blender concepts to measure learning gain.\n- Use GPT4.1 to generate and refine AugGen scaffolded UIs and task-specific guidance scripts.\n- Train simple models (e.g., Logistic Regression) on interaction features to predict task success and compare feature importance across UI conditions.\n- Statistically compare Task Time, Error Rate, NASA TLX, and Learning Gain between AugGen and default UI for novices vs experts."
}

