  "GPT51_suggested_pipeline": "- Split NL4RA into train, validation, and test sets with problem texts and gold LP/ILP/MILP formulations.\n- Implement baseline prompting strategies for LLMs (e.g., zero-shot, few-shot, chain-of-thought) to generate formulations from natural language.\n- Implement the multi-candidate LM4Opt-RA framework to generate multiple candidate formulations and apply ranking/selection.\n- For each method, parse generated outputs to check syntax validity and convert to solver-readable LP/MPS format.\n- Evaluate each generated formulation against the gold formulation using Exact Match and Syntax Accuracy.\n- Solve both gold and generated formulations with a standard solver (e.g., Gurobi) and compute Constraint Feasibility and Objective Gap.\n- Compare LM4Opt-RA against baselines on all metrics and conduct ablations on number of candidates and ranking strategy."
}

