  "GPT51_suggested_pipeline": "- Prepare datasets: standard train/validation/test splits for commonsense (CommonsenseQA, StrategyQA) and arithmetic (GSM8K) QA.\n- Select base models: load pretrained RoPE-based LLaMA2-13B and Mistral-7B in a parameter-efficient fine-tuning framework.\n- Implement baselines: apply standard PEFT methods (e.g., LoRA, prefix tuning) on all attention layers as control configurations.\n- Design RoPE-aware method: decompose attention into frequency components, identify low-frequency components relative to RoPE embeddings, and implement selective adaptation modules.\n- Dynamic layer selection: add a mechanism to choose which layers to adapt (e.g., heuristic based on layer depth or learned gating using a small controller) under a fixed parameter budget.\n- Train models: fine-tune baselines and RoPE-aware variants on the training splits with matched parameter and compute budgets.\n- Evaluate performance: compute Accuracy and Exact Match on validation and test sets for each dataset and method.\n- Analyze efficiency: compare number of trainable parameters, memory footprint, and convergence speed across baselines and RoPE-aware approaches.\n- Run ablations: vary which layers are adapted and whether low-frequency attention components are used to isolate their contributions to performance."
}

